Migrated from EPA STORET Legacy Database- originally reported by Wisconsin DNR
.5" rain 8/6- calm- mostly cloudy- 78 F- excessive weeds- no algae.
Excessive weeds in shallow areas affects props on boats- clear- slight. breeze 95 F- .25" rain 8/13- no algae
Clear- 64 F- slight breeze- weeds protruding lake surface
Clear- 82 F- breezy- excessive weed growth
Clear- slight breeze- excessive weeds- harvester is busy
Partly sunny- breezy- 72 F- best reading ever taken in summer
Mostly sunny- windy- 80 F- no algae bloom
Partly cloudy- slight. breeze- 70 F- weeds worse than last year- harvester working.  Water level: up 2"
Partly cloudy- slight. breeze- 87 F- weeds thick. Water level up 1 7/8"
Clear- slight. breeze- 82 F- weeds.  Water level up 1.75"
Partly cloudy- slight. breeze- 78 F- weeds- shoreline weeds sprayed 7/10.  Water level: Up .25"
Partly cloudy- slight. breeze- 75 F- 3 pr. Canadian Geese with 9 goslings.  Water level: Up .25"
Mostly sunny- calm- 74 F- weedy in areas not sprayed or harvested
Clear- breezy- 76 F- weeds sprayed 8/7- goslings grown up and pesky
Clear- calm- 80 F- humid- weedy in areas not treated or harvested
Clear- calm- 78 F- still weed problem
Partly cloudy- breezy- 72 F- weeds not a problem.  Water level: Up 1.5"
Partly cloudy- slight breeze- weed problem
Clear- slight breeze- 70 F- high amount of weed growth.  Water level: up 2"
Partly cloudy- breezy- 79 F- weedy.  Water level: up 2"
Mostly clear- slight breeze- 88 F- weedy.  Water level: Up 1.25"
Partly cloudy- slight breeze- 73 F- weedy.  Water level: Up .5"
Clear- breezy- 82 F- weedy.  Water level: Up 3/8"
Clear- slight breeze- 84 F- weedy.  Water level: Up .25"
Overcast- breezy- 72 F- weedy.  Water level: Up .25"
Cloudy- slight breeze- 82 F- weedy.  Water level: Up .25"
Clear- slight breeze- weeds under control
Weed problem.  Village is harvesting weeds.
Calm- mostly sunny- weed problem.  Spotted green heron with at least one young.
Water and air are calm- temp is 76 degrees.  Purple martin young left their nest- weed problem is pretty much controlled by harvesting and chemicals.  Water level: Up 1.5"
Water and air is calm- mostly sunny- 76 degrees.  Purple martins do not return to their nests at sundown. Water level: Up .75"
Mostly sunny- breezy- 77 degrees- no weed problem- traffic is light on labor day weekend- geese do not return to lake at evening time- blue heron frequents lake for feeding.  Water even w/dam
Slight breeze- 54 degrees- clear sky. Water level: Up .75"
Breezy- clear sky- air temp 71- ice out 4/10/93
Slight breeze- air temp 74- clear sky- 4-5 broods of geese being raised
Slight breeze- air temp 77- clear sky- more weeds- heavy boat traffic during day
Breezy- clear- air temp 78- 1.5" rain past 24 hours- green Huron in area
Calm- air temp 71- no breeze- partly cloudy- no weeds- young geese
Slight breeze- thin overcast- air temp 78- weed harvester began operations this past week
Calm- clear- air temp 84- worst reading this summer- weed harvester not operating- ran about 5 days this summer- weeds not a problem as in past years
Slight breeze- clear- 84 degrees.  Sighting blue heron feeding along shore line.
90 F- sunny- slight breeze- no noticeable algae.
Sunny- clear- calm- 78 F- no algae
Windy- clear- 65 degrees.  Water level: Up 1.25"
Breezy- partly cloudy.  45 degrees.  Water level: Up 1.5"
Much rain-runoff-lots of material floating around/suspended.
Water color was more black than any of the color choices.
Needed to wait until evening when winds calmed; water more of a black color than other choices
Reading taken after first real busy speedboat day on the lake with lots of churning of the water; water was its usual black color; 3" of rain on one day alone during the rainy week
Scattered rain showers today and yesterday
Little choppy due to wind; waves made it harder to read the disk
Completed this with the help of Don Laine; the 15' and 20' DO values seem to be backwards.  I ran the test on them twice and got the same reading so I must have reversed the bottles at some point.

Observed CLP in creek that empties into the lake; same area but further upstream than the area where we pulled CLP earlier this summer.  Don Laine and I were checking to see if we need to hand-pull more CLP.
Hand-pulled curly-leaf pondweed with Don and Lowell from creek west of public landing
Don Laine worked with me to sample water
The surface of the lake near the shore has its annual greenish-brownish streaks.  Not sure what algae bloom is but that term comes to mind.
Water temp in shallow water very near the shore is 39.5.
Checked inflowing creek near public landing to see if curly leafed pond weed is growing and there's no sign of it yet
Today follows last night's heavy rain of almost 2"
High temps in the 80s!!  Water level a little high because of recent heavy rains.
Lake water was dark after runoff from our 3.6? rain on Sunday.
